(3) Subject to subsection(1), the constitution may provide for (a) the classes of membership and their rights, privileges and obligations; (b) the meetings of the Association , including the delivery and sufficiency of notices of the meetings, quorum, voting,  adjournment and other matters of procedure or conduct of the meetings; (c) the election, qualifications and tenure of office of the President , Vice-President and other office bearers of the Association ; (d) composition, functions, powers and procedures of the committees of the Association ; (e) establishment, powers and functions of the branches of the Association ; and (f) any other matter as the membership may determine.
