(4) A person does not qualify to be elected as a member of the Council if that person— (a) is legally disqualified from performing the functions of a member; (b) has committed any professional misconduct within a period of five years preceding the person’s election as a member; (c) is adjudged bankrupt under any written law; or (d) is convicted of an offence under this Act or any other written law and sentenced to imprisonment for a term exceeding six months without the option of a fine.
